=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_PanB_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with complex oscillator character around 51 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 51.1687
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.0762
  harmonic_regularity: 0.3804
  pitch_clarity: 22.9322
  inharmonicity: 0.0329
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.0463
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: PanB Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/PanB.html
// Tags: PanB, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// You'll only hear the first two channels on a stereo setup.
play({
    #w, x, y, z = PanB.ar(WhiteNoise.ar, LFSaw.kr(0.5, pi), FSinOsc.kr(0.31, 0.5pi), 0.3);
    // decode for 4 channels
    DecodeB2.ar(4, w, x, y, 0.5);
});
